Dow falls 75 points on losses for 3M, Pfizer shares

Shares of 3M and Pfizer are posting losses Wednesday morning, dragging the Dow Jones Industrial Average into negative territory. Shares of 3M MMM, -2.14% and Pfizer PFE, -0.68% are contributing to the blue-chip gauge's intraday decline, as the Dow DJIA, -2.29% was most recently trading 77 points (0.3%) lower. 3M's shares have declined $2.41, or 1.4%, while those of Pfizer have declined $0.34 (0.9%), combining for an approximately 19-point drag on the Dow. Other components contributing significantly to the decline include Goldman Sachs GS, -1.90%, IBM IBM, -3.25%, and Caterpillar CAT, -3.19%. A $1 move in any of the index's 30 components equates to a 6.78-point swing.